articles.title: EU says unilateral trade action unacceptable after Poland, Hungary ban Ukraine grain, food imports - Reuters.com
articles.description: Unilateral action on trade by European Union member states is unacceptable, a European Commission spokesperson said on Sunday, after Poland and Hungary announced bans on grain and other food imports from Ukraine to protect the local agricultural sector.
